        %p Spirulina is a type of blue-green algae that is rich in protein, vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. It is often used as a dietary supplement to support overall health and wellness.
      .bg-green-600.dark:bg-green-700.p-6.rounded-lg.shadow-md
        %h3.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 How can Spirulina benefit my health?
        %p Spirulina has numerous health benefits including boosting the immune system, improving digestion, reducing inflammation, and providing essential nutrients for better energy and vitality.
      .bg-green-600.dark:bg-green-700.p-6.rounded-lg.shadow-md
        %h3.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 Is Spirulina safe to consume?
        %p Yes, Spirulina is generally safe for most people when consumed in appropriate amounts. However, it is always best to consult with a healthcare provider before adding any new supplement to your diet.
      .bg-green-600.dark:bg-green-700.p-6.rounded-lg.shadow-md
        %h3.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 How should I take Spirulina?
        %p Spirulina can be taken in various forms including powder, tablets, and capsules. The recommended dosage varies depending on the form and your specific health needs, so it's important to follow the instructions on the product label or consult with a healthcare provider.

